commit.message: updated ru.po

Fixed  Russian localization

Commit 8e71a769e70df275d69b681b5aa69b7294a4673e accidentally deleted all
messages from ru.po.  The reason was an incorrect charset setting in this
file, so "make update-po" discarded all unrecognized characters.

The ru.po file is recovered and updated.
prepare 0.5.0
localization update

Avoid a never-ending loop if the PIN is locked.

It also skips a token that is not initialized.

	modified:   src/pam_p11.c
fixed CI badges

run CI tests (token without pub key)

	modified:   .github/ci-test.sh

Search for authkey after login.

In order to find  private key, we must first login to the token.
	modified:   src/pam_p11.c

Don't look for the public key in key_verify() function.

If the token does not contain a public key, then the search will fail.  In
the find_key() function, we have already found the relevant key (in the
certificate or as a real public key).
	modified:   src/pam_p11.c
prepare 0.4.0

run CI tests using .eid/authorized_certificates

Softhsm2 is used for tests, private and public key are present in HSM.
	modified:   .github/ci-test.sh

commit.message:
libressl CI test (test-login)

	new file:   .github/setup-libressl.sh
	modified:   .github/workflows/ci.yml

libressl fix for EC keys

	modified:   src/match_openssh.c

run test-login in CI

- Keys for test: RSA:2048 EC:secp256r1 EC:secp384r1 EC:secp521r1
- softhsm is used as pkcs#11 provider
- .ssh/authorized_keys is used for public key placament

	new file:   .github/ci-test.sh
	modified:   .github/workflows/ci.yml

Do not check the login name if the login is given on the command line.

The login name is not available in some cases, in which case the
"getlogin_r()" function will fail.  If we have a login name on
the command line, there is no reason to call this function.

	modified:   src/test.c

CI: compilation test also on ubuntu-22 (openssl 3.0.2)

	modified:   .github/workflows/ci.yml

Simplified EC key comparison (for .ssh/authorized_keys)

Conversion of EC key to internal form is modified, currently works for
openssl 1.1.1 as well as for versions 3.0.2 and 3.0.8.

	modified:   src/match_openssh.c

Fixed incorrect RSA key comparison (for .ssh/authorized_keys)

	modified:   src/match_openssh.c
